cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a Prolog theorem prover for an Intuitionistic Epistemic Logic and discusses the embedding of modal logics into intuitionistic logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves the automatic synthesis of logic systems and the use of candidate definition formula generators. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of Prolog as a theorem prover. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves the use of algorithms for definition formula generation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves the development of a software tool for theorem proving.
